main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Davenport, Iowa on the evening of May 11, 1953.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for 10 minutes,The object was observed at a low altitude and was reported as traveling on a level course,The observer had a significantly high reliability rating of 3 on March 60,The investigation was part of the Project Blue Book initiative by the U.S. Air Force,The document indicates no physical evidence was found during the investigation.
